I admit that I was pleased with that line - that was what convinced me that I had enough of a hook to make the phenomenon into the main anomaly (it was originally the book).



What really impresses me about the article is how thematically consistent it manages to be while also indulging in out-there concept-salad weirdness  Once you've claimed that all human sexual behaviour can be reduced to a set of rigid principles, is it surprising that this reduction is totally arbitrary, esoteric, and unhinged?
附加记录：    

In some ways, this is influenced heavily by Silber's original 1425. The Star Signals self-help book is another example of the essential emptiness of following instructions on how to live one's life that aren't sensible / practical / pragmatic. Linking the theme and imagery was a two-way dialogue between the book extracts and the exploration log (and between those and the initial notes), with each feeding back into the other.



the Stepford Wives realisation that the end-point of sexually-motivated misogyny is the murderous replacement of real women with pliant, submissive automata.
附加记录：    

Yes, and this was what unlocked the ending for me. Thinking this through to its logical conclusion - the PUAs think they want a living sex-doll, but actually are not satisfied by this even when they can create it. But because they don't acknowledge their emotional needs, they are driven to continue their behaviour. Because they treat women entirely as objects, they also treat them as entirely disposable - that led to the ending, where Agent Cooper is literally  into a pit.

I'm really pleased that you  this (for a certain value of enjoy), and really grateful for the detailed and thoughtful comment. Thanks!







